result.formatted_address: 100 Lai Chi Kok Rd, Prince Edward, Hong Kong
result.name: Madam's Kitchen

reviews.text:
Reasonably priced Taiwanese food (around 60hkd for a filling dinner set) with decent quality and good service. The fried chicken was tender on the inside while giving a satisfying crunch. The fried mix (with mushroom, squidball, chicken and a mochi-like thingy) was really satisfying. 
Whats more to the fine food is the warm service. The considerate server paid close attention to her customers, she recommended some food and drinks for us and initiated in giving us what we needed even before our requests. 

Would definitely come back for a casual meal with friends!

Came here for the lunch set. Very good value! I have ordered the Taiwanese Beef Noodles and the meats are in good quality. Layers with slight fat and the texture is tender. I have added a plate of veggies and soft Boiled egg. Both are good too, priced at hkd10 for each is reasonable. Recommend! Probably one of the best Taiwanese food in this district.

We have a nice dinner to celebrate the first victory. Thanks for always supporting me to pass all the tough times. I will always be with you for your tough times too. Feel happy and safe to walk together for this long journey. More and more unreal becomes real. Super super super love you❤️92❤️
A bit salty for the chicken, but taste good.
Good value and good Taiwanese food around the area.

reviews.text: 不錯👍
$35 午餐連凍飲，真係底食夾大件☺️

好失望！蠔仔粥泡飯，湯水是即食麵味精味道；珍珠奶茶及台式咖啡，都是洗杯水似的，奶又稀又有怪味。
雖然開店理念很大很有意思，但事實上真的很不合格。
